{"type": "root", "attrs": {"icon": "SHELF/emit_steam", "tags": "viscousfluids"}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Emit Steam on Collision"], "extent": [46, 74]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Emits steam when a hot fluid comes into contact with a collider."], "extent": [74, 147]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Overview"], "extent": [147, 162], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This tool will take a viscous fluid and apply a secondary steam simulation, where steam is emitted whenever a hot fluid comes into contact with collision objects. You would typically use this tool to simulate lava coming in contact with a wet surface and evaporating the water."], "extent": [162, 443]}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Using Emit Steam on Collision"], "extent": [443, 479], "body": [{"type": "ord_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "ord", "indent": 0, "text": ["Select the hot fluid to emit steam from."], "extent": [479, 524]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "ord", "indent": 0, "text": ["Click the ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "SHELF/emit_steam", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/shelf/SHELF/emit_steam"}, {"type": "ui", "text": ["Emit Steam"]}, " tool on the Viscous Fluids tab. "], "extent": [524, 608], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["For specific parameter information, see the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/dop/smokeobject", "type": "link", "text": ["Smoke Object"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/smokeobject"}, " help page."], "extent": [608, 704]}], "container": true}], "container": true}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/shelf/emitsteamoncollision.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "extent": [704, 752]}, {"type": "task_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "task", "indent": 0, "text": [" Control how much steam is emitted"], "role": "item", "extent": [752, 794], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Modify the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Scale"]}, " parameter on the ", {"type": "code", "text": ["density"]}, " ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Source Volume"]}, " of the ", {"type": "code", "text": ["source_density_from_steam_source"]}, " DOP. This will adjust how much steam is emitted globally."], "extent": [794, 969]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["You can also adjust the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Scale"]}, " parameter on the ", {"type": "code", "text": ["create_density"]}, " node in the ", {"type": "code", "text": ["steam_source"]}, " object."], "extent": [969, 1086]}], "container": true}, {"ext": null, "type": "task", "indent": 0, "text": [" Create thin and wispy smoke"], "role": "item", "extent": [1086, 1122], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Use the controls on the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Shape"]}, " tab of the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/dop/pyrosolver", "type": "link", "text": ["Pyro Solver"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/pyrosolver"}, ". For thin and wispy smoke, you'd want high dissipation and high-frequency turbulence and disturbance."], "extent": [1122, 1312]}], "container": true}, {"ext": null, "type": "task", "indent": 0, "text": [" Create thick smoke"], "role": "item", "extent": [1312, 1339], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Use the controls on the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Shape"]}, " tab of the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/dop/pyrosolver", "type": "link", "text": ["Pyro Solver"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/pyrosolver"}, ". For thick smoke, you'd want low or no dissipation and lower frequency turbulence."], "extent": [1339, 1506]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}], "title": ["Emit Steam on Collision"], "summary": ["Emits steam when a hot fluid comes into contact with a collider."]}